process help=*
parm inp        type=(string,99)
parm out        type=(string,99)

PARM doavg       TYPE=INTEGER                       DEFAULT=1
PARM dogainoff   TYPE=INTEGER                       DEFAULT=1
PARM dostretch   TYPE=INTEGER                       DEFAULT=0
PARM sgcolumn    TYPE=INTEGER                       DEFAULT=0
!parm xdoavg      type=keyword default=0 count=(0:1) valid=doavg default=--
!parm xdogainoff  type=keyword default=1 count=(0:1) valid=dogainoff default=--
!parm xdostretch  type=keyword default=0 count=(0:1) valid=dostretch default=--

parm subnl      type=int default=19
parm subns      type=int default=11
parm skip       type=int default=5

parm fileformat type=string valid=("vicar","geotiff") default="vicar"
end-proc

.title
VICAR Program unstreak - removes streaks
.help
PURPOSE

     UNSTREAK removes streaks.

.PAGE
TAE COMMAND LINE FORMAT

     unstreak INP=I OUT=O
     
     where

     I is a VICAR input images
     O is a VICAR output images

.PAGE
OPERATION

     UNSTREAK removes streaks.
   
.PAGE

RESTRICTIONS

     None known.

.PAGE
WRITTEN BY:            W. L. Bunch, R. Nathan

COGNIZANT PROGRAMMER:  W. L. Bunch, R. Nathan

REVISIONS: 
    Nov 10 2003
    Initial version

.level1

.var inp

Input file.

.var out

Output file.

.var doavg

Flag enabling offset correction.

.var dogainoff

Flag enabling gain correction.

.var dostretch

Flag enabling a linear stretch.

.var subnl

Subwindow height, used by gain correction.

.var subns

Subwindow width, used by gain correction.

.var skip

Subwindow sampling skip, used by gain correction.

.var fileformat

In/out file format, one of (vicar, geotiff).

.level2

.var skip

Subwindow sampling skip, used by gain correction. This is the distance
between the window tops.

.var fileformat

In/out file format, one of (vicar, geotiff). GeoTIFF files are
converted to VICAR (using VTIFF3) before processing.

.end
